This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as word similarity and document clustering, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel generative model for learning text embeddings, which involves optimization algorithms and machine learning techniques, indicating that it may also be relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of embeddings in information retrieval (IR) and computer vision (CV) tasks, which suggests that it could potentially be relevant to the cs.IR and cs.CV sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper's focus on unsupervised learning and optimization algorithms suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
